cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CV. 

The paper deals with a machine learning algorithm (kernel PCA) in a distributed setting, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), data mining (cs.DM), or computer vision (cs.CV). However, since the focus is on developing a communication efficient algorithm for kernel PCA, cs.LG and cs.DC are the most likely categories. The use of subspace embedding and adaptive sampling techniques also suggests a potential fit with cs.DS and cs.DM. Finally, the experiments with real-world datasets could also make cs.CV a possible category.
